[msg95, msg94, msg93, msg92, msg91]\nReverse: [msg91, msg92, msg93, msg94, msg95
]\nnextCursor = 91\n\nThis is correct. The UI would prepend older messages to th
e beginning of the list.\n\nNow, the `ImBloc._onLoadMessages` does:\n```dart\nif
(event.cursor == null) {\n  _messages.clear();\n}\n_messages.insertAll(0, result
.items);\n```\n\nWait, this is wrong for pagination! If we load the first page (
cursor=null), _messages.clear() happens, then _messages.insertAll(0, [msg96, msg
97, msg98, msg99, msg100]). That gives [msg96, msg97, msg98, msg99, msg100]. Goo
d.\n\nIf we load the next page (cursor=96), _messages.insertAll(0, [msg91, msg92
, msg93, msg94, msg95]). That gives [msg91, msg92, msg93, msg94, msg95, msg96, m
