nmodifiable(_messages)));\n```\n\nThis adds the message to the END of the list. 
But if there are already messages loaded and the list is in ascending order (old
est to newest), adding to the end is correct for new messages.\n\nWait, but `_on
LoadMessages` does `_messages.insertAll(0, result.items)`. If result.items is in
ascending order [oldest, ..., newest], then inserting at 0 puts them at the begi
nning. After loading page 1, _messages = [page1_oldest, ..., page1_newest]. Afte
r receiving a new message, _messages = [page1_oldest, ..., page1_newest, new_msg
]. That\'s correct.\n\nAfter loading page 2 (older messages), _messages = [page2
_oldest, ..., page2_newest, page1_oldest, ..., page1_newest, new_msg]. That\'s a
lso correct.\n\nOK, the message ordering logic is fine.\n\nNow let me think abou
